 {"id":"frankenredis-vhkl","title":"[MOCK] Lua redis.breakpoint/debug still return no-op stubs","description":"Evidence: crates/fr-command/src/lua_eval.rs:2487 and :2491 both return nil with comments \"No-op: debugging stub\".\n\nCurrent gap: the Lua API advertises debugger hooks, but the evaluator silently swallows them instead of providing Redis-compatible debugging behavior or an explicit unsupported path.\n\nReal impl path: replace the placeholder branches in crates/fr-command/src/lua_eval.rs with real debugger integration or a deliberate Redis-compatible error/feature gate surfaced through the runtime scripting path in crates/fr-runtime/src/lib.rs.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:43:03.074231819Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T09:11:29.597130985Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T09:11:29.595040889Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}

