+{"id":"frankenredis-7q4b","title":"redis parity: ACL DELUSER should disconnect clients authenticated as the removed user","description":"Upstream redis/tests/unit/acl.tcl expects ACL DELUSER to close connections that are currently authenticated as the deleted user. Local handle_acl_deluser in crates/fr-runtime/src/lib.rs removes the user from AuthState but does not queue or apply any client disconnects, so active sessions can keep running after their user is deleted. Match Redis by revoking those sessions when DELUSER succeeds.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:53:28.852266681Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T07:17:40.395831831Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T07:17:40.395831831Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenredis-kw56","title":"redis parity: ACL channel patterns should be stored, rendered, and enforce revocation","description":"Local AuthState::set_user only special-cases &* at crates/fr-runtime/src/lib.rs:835-839 and ignores literal and wildcard channel patterns. Upstream redis/tests/unit/acl.tcl exercises resetchannels with literals and patterns, expects ACL LIST to render resetchannels before channel specs, and expects subscribers to be dropped when channel permission is revoked. Implement channel-pattern storage, rendering, authorization, and revocation parity.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:11:24.699383840Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:24:23.609589005Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T08:24:23.609589005Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenredis-qc70","title":"redis parity: Lua redis.call('CONFIG', 'GET') returns dictionary","description":"Newer Redis versions return a dictionary/map from redis.call('CONFIG', 'GET') instead of a flat array. Align Lua evaluator.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T10:00:41.968206983Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:02:36.037205108Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T08:02:36.037205108Z","close_reason":"Duplicate of frankenredis-8xm7; already implemented","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenredis-zcd9","title":"redis parity: ACL LOG should preserve lua context for script authorization failures","description":"Upstream redis/tests/unit/acl.tcl expects ACL LOG context=lua when a scripted command trips ACL enforcement. Local fr-runtime ACL logging always emits context='toplevel', so script-originated denials cannot be distinguished from normal commands. Carry the Lua execution context into ACL log entries with Redis-compatible context and object fields.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:53:41.192597825Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T07:42:38.442459472Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T07:42:38.442459472Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
